The paper deals with algorithms for discrete Gaussian sampling, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). It also involves the study of lattices, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents reductions between different problems, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
